						               													<description>Towers is a game with elements of chess and checkers, played on an 8X8 board&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players start with 15 Towers and one Castellans, with both moving like the chess Rook, and may leap orthogonally over an adjacent piece, landing on the next empty cell.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Castellans may additionally step a single cell diagonally, but not to the goal cell, the corner to a player's left, without capturing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player may not enter their own goal cell. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;CAPTURE - There are two ways of capture:&amp;#10;    Custodian, sandwiching an opponent's piece orthgonally between two of your own pieces, or by Intervention; where a piece steps between two orthogonally placed enemy pieces, it captures them both.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is possible to move so as to capture in more than one direction at a time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
